<TITLE> Dhaka stocks go steady </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 7 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka Stock Exchange remained more or less steady on the closing day of the week though gainers dominated the day's trading session. Thursday's trading was marked with a sharp fall but the market recovered immediately and maintained a steady pace across the day. Banks, which heavily influences the market movement, gained slightly, with non-banking financial institutions joining in. Insurers edged down though life insurance companies witnessed a hike while power sector remained roughly steady. Mutual funds shook off Wednesday's losses while textile sector crept down after gaining for the last two days. DSE's benchmark general index or DGEN dropped 27 points at the opening due to ex-dividend trade and price adjustment of Uttara Bank. It ended slightly lower by 5.98 points or 0.23 percent to 2493.58. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2078.44, slipping 0.66 points or 0.23 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 crept up 4.52 points or 0.23 percent to finish on 1925.03. Gainers outnumbered losers 183 to 51 while seven issues held steady. Turnover on the country's premier bourse clocked Tk 4.36 billion with 32,038,578 shares changing hands. Summit Power remained the turnover leader with shares worth Tk 617.036 million traded. It gained 4.08 percent to Tk 1402.75. Titas Gas followed with a turnover of Tk 413.434 million to edge down 0.83 percent on Tk 531.50. Beximco ended on Tk 277.40, slipping 0.85 percent. It had shares worth Tk 313.441 million traded. Z category issue Bextex Ltd saw turnover worth Tk 272.231 million to surge 7.04 percent to close at Tk 45.60. Eastern Housing Ltd had shares worth Tk 188.467 million traded and ended on Tk 684.25, up 10.98 percent. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardBeximco Synthetics, Bangladesh Online, Beximco Pharmaceuticals and S Alam Cold Rolled Steels finished higher. Shinepukur Ceramics fell on selling pressure. Chittagong Stock Exchange Gains in textile, ICT and paper shares drove the indices on the port city bourse to end higher. The CSCX or selective categories index rose 50.23 points or 0.95 percent to close at 5296.44. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8175.22, rising 81.49 points or 1 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip gained 55.83 points or 0.88 percent to finish at 6342.68. Turnover slightly rose to Tk 552.858 million from 538.301 million from the previous day. Of the traded issues, 107 advanced, 37 declined with four scrips unchanged. Bextex Ltd topped the turnover board with shares worth Tk 51.82 million changing hands. Summit Power, Shinepukur Ceramics, Beximco Synthetics and Titas Gas were the other turnover leaders.
